Rinse okra and cut head and tail end off of each okra. Chop okra into small pieces. In a small mixing bowl combine okra, salt, chili powder and asafoetida powder. In a medium size skillet over medium-high flame heat oil, add black mustard seeds. Cook until they pop. Add okra mixture to skillet and cover. Let fry 10 to 15 minutes. Serve hot.